    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tables designed for a game similar to billiards called bagatelle. These tables have a semicircular area at one end in which there are nine numbered holes or cups, each number signifying the points to be scored by pocketing a ball. The table width is usually one-third of its length.</Note_Text>
